@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{markdown-mode-extras.el} extends @samp{markdown-mode} with commands for
clipboard conversion, section manipulation, and link editing.  Much of
the package revolves around interoperability between Markdown and Org
mode, using Pandoc as the conversion engine.  If you frequently copy
content between Org and Markdown files, or paste formatted text from
the web into a Markdown buffer, these commands save considerable
manual reformatting.

The main capabilities are:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Clipboard conversion}: paste clipboard content while converting
between Org, Markdown, and HTML formats via Pandoc
(@ref{Clipboard conversion}).
@item
@strong{Section operations}: extract or copy the body of the current
Markdown section (@ref{Section operations}).
@item
@strong{Link editing}: strip the URL from a Markdown link, keeping only the
description text (@ref{Link editing}).
@end itemize

