@node Getting section content
@section Getting section content

@findex markdown-mode-extras-get-section
The function @code{markdown-mode-extras-get-section} returns the body of a
Markdown section as a string.  If the optional SECTION argument (a
heading title) is provided, the function searches the buffer for that
heading; otherwise it uses the section containing point.  Section
boundaries are determined by @code{markdown-outline-previous} and
@code{markdown-outline-next}.

@node Deleting a link
@section Deleting a link

@findex markdown-mode-extras-delete-link
The function @code{markdown-mode-extras-delete-link} removes the entire
Markdown link at point (@samp{[description](url)}) from the buffer and
returns the link's description text.  It uses @code{markdown-link-at-pos}
to locate the link boundaries.  This function is used by
@code{markdown-mode-extras-remove-url-in-link} (@ref{Link editing}).

